16th of February…

do set_background("calleDiaInvierno")
As I stepped outside, I noticed how cold it was, and I saw him waiting.
The moment he looked at me, he let out a smile.

Luckily for me, the first thing we did that day was go to the café we used to frequent. It had become a habit to go there.

do set_background("negroo")
While I sipped my beloved cappuccino to warm up and try to calm my nerves, he talked about his family, things that happened to some of his classmates, and other topics.

I tried to look at him, I swear I tried to meet his eyes, but I simply couldn’t. I was incapable of doing so knowing that he had already read my letter.
He already knew how I felt, but I didn’t know whether those feelings were returned or not. And that was slowly killing me.

Definitely, I was a masochist.

I couldn’t complain, knowing full well that I was the one who had told him not to say anything about the letter or its contents until we were alone. And I didn’t know how to bring up the subject.
I suppose that if I didn’t do it, he would. Sooner or later.

do set_background("parqueInvierno")
After a couple hours, we reached the park, the one we would often find ourselves in.

It was already dark, even though it was around 8:00 PM, and it was cold. Very cold.
Not even the velvet hoodie I was wearing was enough to keep me warm. I hugged myself, hoping the chills would lessen.
Failed attempt.
Honestly, I hate being so sensitive to the cold.

Luckily, or unfortunately, he noticed. And he hugged me.
Immediately, I felt something rise. My face was red. Because of him. Silly.
Slowly, I pulled away from him, and we sat on an empty bench..

I was wrong to think that my nerves had left my body.

