That’s how I managed to give the letter in which I confessed my feelings to the boy I liked, and two days later, I became his girlfriend. It became official.
I’d be lying if I said it was the best day of my life, since that was the day my ostomy was removed. But if it wasn’t the very best, it was definitely one of the best days I’ve ever had.

Since then, we have been practically inseparable.
If there was ever a problem, we always tried to solve it calmly, with love above all else.

And so, almost without realizing it, winter slipped away, making way for the bright and warm arrival of summer.

I remember how, sometimes, he would slowly lean in to try to kiss me, and when he saw I wasn’t ready, he would simply apologize and say not to worry, that he would wait as long as necessary until I was prepared.
Until one summer day.

